WEBVTT

00:12.241 --> 00:15.448
[ Wind blowing ]

00:45.482 --> 00:48.517
[ Wind whistling ]

01:00.103 --> 01:03.000
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

01:36.862 --> 01:39.413
[ Music builds, continues ]

02:20.827 --> 02:23.379
[ Music builds, continues ]

02:45.620 --> 02:48.517
[ Music slows, continues ]

02:54.620 --> 02:57.586
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:05.344 --> 03:07.793
DARLENE:
Okay. I'm coming back.

03:08.689 --> 03:10.275
GRETCHEN:
Oh, do you need these?

03:10.310 --> 03:11.793
DARLENE: Yeah. One sec.
I'll take a look at --

03:11.827 --> 03:14.206
Oh.
Oh, no.

03:14.241 --> 03:16.103
I can't serve this to people,
not even the kids.

03:16.137 --> 03:17.655
The kids are not even
gonna eat this.

03:17.689 --> 03:19.413
Are you --
You've got to be joking.

03:19.448 --> 03:22.689
It's cake -- and kids.
The -- The messier the better.

03:22.724 --> 03:24.586
-I mean, I'm sorry about that.
-All right.

03:24.620 --> 03:26.344
-Fine, fine, fine, fine, fine.
-They're gonna love it, though.

03:26.379 --> 03:28.137
What, are you mad?

03:29.103 --> 03:31.413
-Uh, no. No. No.
-What's wrong?

03:31.448 --> 03:33.689
[ Sighs ]
I just...

03:33.724 --> 03:35.551
This -- This is hard, you know?

03:35.586 --> 03:37.413
It's -- It's just hard.
Sorry.

03:37.448 --> 03:39.344
First time hosting Christmas
in 20 years.

03:39.379 --> 03:41.137
-Gee. Why would that be hard?
-Yeah.

03:41.172 --> 03:43.793
I do not know what I was
thinking, taking all this on.

03:43.827 --> 03:45.172
It's so stupid.

03:45.206 --> 03:46.620
I mean, I used to be really good
at this,

03:46.655 --> 03:48.517
and then I just lost
all my skills.

03:48.551 --> 03:50.758
You have not!
You're -- You're fine!

03:50.793 --> 03:53.310
Listen. As my mother used to
say, the queen ain't coming.

03:53.344 --> 03:55.103
It's just us --
just your people.

03:55.137 --> 03:56.379
And you know
what we're gonna do?

03:56.413 --> 03:57.551
We're gonna drink
too much coffee.

03:57.586 --> 03:58.758
We're gonna spoil the kids.

03:58.793 --> 04:00.517
We're gonna open gifts.

04:00.551 --> 04:03.103
We're gonna eat so much
that we have to unhook our bras.

04:03.551 --> 04:06.241
And then fuckin' Julie's gonna
put everybody to work

04:06.275 --> 04:07.344
to clean it up.

04:07.379 --> 04:08.620
It's gonna be great.

04:08.655 --> 04:10.413
It's gonna be fine, all right?

04:10.448 --> 04:12.172
You're right. You're right.
You're right.

04:12.206 --> 04:13.482
Okay.

04:13.517 --> 04:16.517
Now have a bark cookie.

04:16.551 --> 04:19.379
-[ Laughs ]
-I'm sorry it's not booze.

04:19.413 --> 04:20.655
Yeah.

04:21.275 --> 04:22.482
-GRETCHEN: Oh!
-DARLENE: Mm.

04:22.517 --> 04:23.689
GRETCHEN:
Is that my cue to leave?

04:23.724 --> 04:26.137
DARLENE:
I think it is.

04:26.172 --> 04:27.655
-Well --
-Oh, shit.

04:27.689 --> 04:29.034
-What? What? What's wrong.
-Damn. Damn, damn, damn.

04:29.068 --> 04:30.241
-No. Hang on.
-Is everything all right?

04:30.275 --> 04:32.275
Yeah.
I think so.

04:32.310 --> 04:36.275
I-I think this is finally
finished uploading.

04:36.310 --> 04:37.793
-GRETCHEN: What is it?
-DARLENE: Hang on.

04:39.068 --> 04:41.103
INTERVIEWER: This month
is the 20th anniversary

04:41.137 --> 04:43.068
of Sally's disappearance.

04:43.103 --> 04:45.310
How has it been for --

04:47.862 --> 04:49.413
Why do they call it
an anniversary,

04:49.448 --> 04:51.724
like it's something
to celebrate?

04:54.310 --> 04:55.448
Whoo!

04:55.482 --> 04:56.758
-Oh, man!
-[ Laughs ]

04:56.793 --> 04:58.379
Be careful!

04:58.413 --> 05:00.379
-Okay! Bye-bye!
-Don't slip down those stairs!

05:00.413 --> 05:03.241
And I love you, and thank you
for everything today!

05:03.275 --> 05:06.137
-Whoo!
-Bye, Gretchen! Drive safely!

05:06.172 --> 05:07.241
Ooh.

05:07.275 --> 05:09.206
[ Latch clicks, wind whistling ]

05:09.241 --> 05:10.517
Mm!

05:37.620 --> 05:40.517
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

06:30.586 --> 06:32.379
[ Music continues ]

06:32.413 --> 06:35.655
INTERVIEWER: I can only imagine
the pain you must be in.

06:35.689 --> 06:39.586
DARLENE:
Well, I-I have had the honor

06:39.620 --> 06:42.724
of working with other searching
families over the years.

06:42.758 --> 06:46.413
And -- And for most of us,

06:46.448 --> 06:50.206
the...the hardest part is...

06:50.241 --> 06:52.206
is the not knowing,

06:52.241 --> 06:55.379
the daily void
of just not knowing.

06:55.413 --> 06:59.586
But Sally is always going to be
alive to me

06:59.620 --> 07:01.344
until I know different.

07:01.379 --> 07:04.586
And I will never,
never stop looking for her.

07:04.620 --> 07:07.137
INTERVIEWER:
You're so brave.

07:07.172 --> 07:09.586
What can people do
if they have any information?

07:09.620 --> 07:13.344
DARLENE: They can contact me
through my website --

07:17.655 --> 07:19.758
[ Music continues ]

07:21.517 --> 07:23.793
Oh, my sweet girl.

07:36.551 --> 07:39.172
[ Music builds, continues ]

08:15.310 --> 08:18.724
[ Wind whistling,
wood creaking ]

08:35.551 --> 08:37.482
[ Knock on door ]

08:49.103 --> 08:51.379
[ Knock on door ]

08:54.275 --> 08:56.482
[ Doorbell rings ]

08:57.862 --> 08:59.482
What...

09:06.344 --> 09:07.482
[ Knock on door ]

09:07.517 --> 09:10.310
[ Wind whistling ]

09:10.344 --> 09:11.448
Jack?

09:11.482 --> 09:14.068
JACK:
Hey, Darlene. I...

09:14.103 --> 09:16.448
I'm sorry I scared you.

09:16.482 --> 09:19.482
Well, what --
what are you doing here?

09:19.517 --> 09:22.103
JACK:
My truck got stuck in the snow.

09:22.137 --> 09:23.586
Wait.
What?

09:23.620 --> 09:26.034
-It -- Oh!
-I lost control on Rogers

09:26.068 --> 09:28.034
and just skidded out
into the snow.

09:28.068 --> 09:33.103
And then I-I saw I was a block
from your place, so...

09:33.137 --> 09:34.793
Well, come in! Come in!
It's freezing!

09:34.827 --> 09:37.172
-Thank you. Thank you.
-[ Exhales sharply ]

09:37.206 --> 09:39.793
Why don't you call Shane
or Lisa?

09:39.827 --> 09:42.344
My phone died.
I am 0 for 2.

09:42.379 --> 09:43.586
[ Chuckles ]

09:43.620 --> 09:47.413
Well, I-I didn't know
you were coming.

09:48.241 --> 09:49.758
Wait.
Was I supposed to know?

09:49.793 --> 09:54.137
I was trying to surprise
everybody, so, um...

09:54.172 --> 09:56.586
Surprise.
[ Chuckles ]

09:59.482 --> 10:01.310
Hey.

10:01.344 --> 10:02.758
Come on.

10:05.586 --> 10:07.655
-[ Exhales deeply ]
-[ Chuckles softly ]

10:09.551 --> 10:12.413
-Good to see you, kid.
-[ Laughs ]

10:12.448 --> 10:14.655
-It's been a minute.
-Nineteen years.

10:14.689 --> 10:16.137
-You believe that?
-Ah.

10:16.172 --> 10:18.758
Well, I mean,
what's a couple decades

10:18.793 --> 10:21.827
between, you know, ex-family?

10:21.862 --> 10:24.310
So because your sister and I
didn't work out, I'm --

10:24.344 --> 10:26.137
I'm ex-family?

10:29.482 --> 10:30.655
[ Gasps ]
I'm so sorry.

10:30.689 --> 10:32.379
May I please take your coat?

10:32.413 --> 10:33.827
Oh, no, no, no.
That's okay.

10:33.862 --> 10:35.758
I'm still a little cold, so...

10:35.793 --> 10:37.206
I imagine.

10:37.241 --> 10:38.551
Let's get something
to warm you up.

10:38.586 --> 10:40.137
-Um...
-Yeah. Sounds good.

10:40.172 --> 10:43.137
How about some tea?
It's actually strictly --

10:43.172 --> 10:46.137
It's strictly chamomile
around here these days.

10:46.172 --> 10:47.517
The kids told me.

10:47.551 --> 10:48.689
Yeah.

10:48.724 --> 10:51.275
I actually just hit 19 years.

10:51.310 --> 10:54.103
It's, um...

10:54.137 --> 10:56.103
Well, I should've done it
a lot sooner, right?

10:56.137 --> 10:57.413
But...

10:57.448 --> 11:00.655
Well, you look great.

11:00.689 --> 11:03.482
No.
I mean reallygreat.

11:03.517 --> 11:05.344
You're such a...

11:05.379 --> 11:08.310
And I-I heard
that you were hosting again,

11:08.344 --> 11:10.551
so, you know, I...

11:10.586 --> 11:13.379
I figured it would be okay.

11:14.206 --> 11:16.413
Oh, you thought this would be

11:16.448 --> 11:18.827
enough of a-a buffer
for you and Julie.

11:18.862 --> 11:21.310
I know it's a stretch.
I admit it.

11:21.344 --> 11:23.068
But, you know,
I never got Christmas

11:23.103 --> 11:24.793
-with Lisa and Shane again.
-I know.

11:24.827 --> 11:28.103
I just want to be with them,
you know?

11:28.137 --> 11:32.206
Look.
I can keep the peace with Julie.

11:32.586 --> 11:34.448
I want to make things right.

11:35.448 --> 11:38.379
I was gonna make it a surprise.

11:38.413 --> 11:42.172
You know, stay at the motel
and surprise everyone

11:42.206 --> 11:44.689
with a big bag of presents
in the morning.

11:44.724 --> 11:46.758
-Oh. [ Clicks tongue, chuckles ]
-But...

11:46.793 --> 11:49.103
Well, I'm not just here
to see them, you know?

11:50.137 --> 11:53.482
I have a lot to make up for it
with you, too, and...

11:53.517 --> 11:55.103
I know that.

11:58.586 --> 12:00.689
I'll get you your tea.

12:02.413 --> 12:04.551
So, you hungry?

12:04.586 --> 12:06.344
JACK:
Always.

12:06.379 --> 12:08.206
DARLENE:
I remember.

12:08.241 --> 12:09.793
[ Microwave beeps ]

12:09.827 --> 12:11.827
Ooh. Okay.
Got it.

12:11.862 --> 12:13.793
-[ Microwave closes ]
-All right.

12:13.827 --> 12:15.655
-Thank you.
-En joie.

12:15.689 --> 12:17.793
[ Chuckles softly ]

12:17.827 --> 12:19.620
[ Wind whistling ]

12:19.655 --> 12:22.517
Oh, God.
Oh, it's amazing.

12:22.551 --> 12:24.793
You have to give me the recipe.

12:24.827 --> 12:27.068
-The recipe?
-Mm.

12:27.103 --> 12:29.344
I'm sorry.
Who -- Who are you?

12:29.379 --> 12:32.482
[ Clears throat ]
Well...

12:33.517 --> 12:35.724
-Um...
-Thank you.

12:35.758 --> 12:39.103
...I'm gonna need you
to call Julie...

12:39.137 --> 12:41.034
-[ Clears throat ]
-...and get her blessing

12:41.068 --> 12:42.586
before you stay for Christmas.

12:42.620 --> 12:44.586
Why?
It's your house.

12:44.620 --> 12:47.172
Jack, I'm not kidding.

12:47.620 --> 12:49.689
You have to call her.

12:49.724 --> 12:51.724
But...not tonight.

12:51.758 --> 12:54.482
-She would rip you --
-[ Chuckles ]

12:54.517 --> 12:58.517
Tonight, you know, you can --
you can stay here.

12:58.551 --> 13:00.034
I mean, obviously.

13:00.068 --> 13:02.344
I don't know where else
you would stay.

13:02.379 --> 13:04.206
I-I, uh...

13:04.241 --> 13:06.448
I-I'd offer you Sally's room,
but --

13:06.482 --> 13:09.068
No. No, no, no, no, no.
No. Of course.

13:09.103 --> 13:14.379
But, however, I can offer you
my super-swank sofa,

13:14.413 --> 13:16.758
which is actually --
It's actually pretty comfy...

13:16.793 --> 13:19.206
-Sounds great. Sounds great.
-...once you make it up.

13:19.241 --> 13:21.758
Hey.
One second.

13:32.655 --> 13:34.275
-[ Laughs ]
-Merry Christmas.

13:34.310 --> 13:36.379
You still love playing Santa,
don't you?

13:36.413 --> 13:39.724
I hope you still like
mint patties.

13:39.758 --> 13:42.172
I do.

13:42.206 --> 13:44.241
I do.
They're simple but classic.

13:44.275 --> 13:46.551
[ Both laugh ]

13:46.586 --> 13:48.620
This is beautiful.
Look.

13:48.655 --> 13:50.413
-Did you wrap this?
-Uh...

13:50.448 --> 13:53.793
Oh, you didn't do it, did you?
You didn't do this.

13:53.827 --> 13:56.413
Let's see.

14:02.724 --> 14:06.137
Our Christmas Eve reading
and chocolate eating.

14:07.655 --> 14:10.172
Oh, Jack.

14:11.827 --> 14:14.137
This is very sweet, but I --

14:14.172 --> 14:16.724
Hey.
It was a family tradition.

14:16.758 --> 14:20.137
No, it wasn't.
You started it.

14:20.172 --> 14:22.724
You gave everyone the book
and chocolates

14:22.758 --> 14:27.620
so they wouldn't notice that you
gave mea book and chocolates.

14:29.344 --> 14:30.793
Maybe.

14:30.827 --> 14:32.068
Mm-hmm.

14:35.413 --> 14:37.827
So how about you?
Hmm?

14:37.862 --> 14:39.758
Girlfriend?

14:39.793 --> 14:43.000
Yeah. We're going steady
and everything.

14:43.448 --> 14:45.137
You think she'll go to the prom
with me?

14:45.172 --> 14:47.034
-[ Laughs ]
-Oh, you know,

14:47.068 --> 14:51.068
I mean, after our
super-fulfilling marriages...

14:51.103 --> 14:54.137
Really odd that we wouldn't rush
to commit again, huh?

14:54.172 --> 14:56.172
I guess I just...

14:56.206 --> 14:59.068
I just never found someone
who could quote Oscar Wilde

14:59.103 --> 15:03.413
while shit-talking in the corner
at a party quite like you could.

15:03.448 --> 15:05.620
[ Both laugh ]

15:15.206 --> 15:18.689
I should never have left
the way I did.

15:21.551 --> 15:26.482
It has haunted me
all these years.

15:26.862 --> 15:29.241
-It's haunted you?
-Yeah.

15:30.551 --> 15:32.724
It's very Heathcliff
on the moors.

15:32.758 --> 15:34.068
[ Chuckles ]

15:37.724 --> 15:39.793
I'm serious.

15:39.827 --> 15:42.103
[ Wind whistling ]

15:45.862 --> 15:47.551
This book looks wonderful.

15:47.586 --> 15:49.551
It is.

15:50.620 --> 15:52.379
So, um...

15:54.379 --> 15:56.137
...how is Julie?

15:58.482 --> 15:59.551
She's good.

15:59.586 --> 16:01.137
Mm-hmm.

16:01.172 --> 16:04.137
She's really good.
She's...

16:04.172 --> 16:05.413
She's still really bossy.

16:05.448 --> 16:07.724
-[ Laughs ]
-But you know what?

16:07.758 --> 16:12.551
That came in quite handy, uh...

16:12.586 --> 16:15.413
the mornings I couldn't get out
of bed and...

16:18.344 --> 16:20.448
She's a really good sister.

16:20.482 --> 16:22.310
Yeah.

16:22.344 --> 16:25.827
Did -- Did --
Did you ever, um...

16:25.862 --> 16:27.137
-Tell her?
-Yeah.

16:27.172 --> 16:28.275
No.

16:28.689 --> 16:30.241
No.

16:30.275 --> 16:32.758
What good would that have done
for her?

16:32.793 --> 16:35.275
-Mm-hmm.
-Me unburdening myself

16:35.310 --> 16:37.379
at her expense with the kid --

16:37.413 --> 16:38.551
I -- No.

16:39.517 --> 16:41.241
You know, um...

16:44.137 --> 16:48.689
...I-I've -- I've thought about
our night a lot.

16:48.724 --> 16:50.034
[ Thunder rumbling ]

16:50.068 --> 16:52.379
I know we -- we were both
a mess,

16:52.413 --> 16:56.551
and...we were all
grieving Sally.

16:56.586 --> 16:58.206
But I'd been wanting you.

16:58.241 --> 17:00.275
I'd been wanting you
for so long.

17:00.310 --> 17:01.793
But th-- But you left.

17:01.827 --> 17:04.068
I couldn't ask you to leave Ed.

17:04.103 --> 17:06.344
-I wasn't gonna leave Ed.
-Oh. Ouch.

17:06.379 --> 17:08.448
It doesn't mean I didn't...

17:12.793 --> 17:15.827
Uh...

17:15.862 --> 17:18.724
I think we just met too late,
you know?

17:20.103 --> 17:23.068
[ Exhales deeply ]

17:23.103 --> 17:26.137
So, Lisa tells me your work
is going really well.

17:26.172 --> 17:27.827
Yeah.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

17:27.862 --> 17:30.413
I have to turn down projects.

17:30.448 --> 17:32.620
-Really? Wow.
-Yeah.

17:32.655 --> 17:36.034
I was sorry to hear
that you had to quit work.

17:36.068 --> 17:37.655
-[ Thunder crashes ]
-DARLENE: Oh.

17:37.689 --> 17:39.689
JACK:
Oh, and it was just snowing.

17:41.344 --> 17:45.206
-DARLENE: Oh, my gosh.
-[ Thunder rumbling ]

17:45.241 --> 17:47.275
-Thundersnow.
-Yeah.

17:47.310 --> 17:49.655
God. It's been years
since I've seen that.

17:49.689 --> 17:51.310
I know.
You'd never think

17:51.344 --> 17:54.103
those two things
would go together, would you?

17:54.137 --> 17:55.620
It just...

17:55.655 --> 17:59.620
It just makes the most
beautiful, dangerous sight.

17:59.655 --> 18:03.551
[ Wind whistling,
thunder crashing ]

18:10.482 --> 18:14.137
I forgot your tea.
I'm so sorry.

18:21.517 --> 18:24.275
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

18:25.827 --> 18:28.482
Well done.
[ Chuckles ]

18:30.103 --> 18:32.344
So, I got to admit --
You're making me feel lazy.

18:32.379 --> 18:34.758
I mean, look at all of this.

18:34.793 --> 18:38.034
"Awarded to Darlene Hagen
in grateful recognition

18:38.068 --> 18:40.793
for your service to missing
children and their families."

18:40.827 --> 18:42.275
Wow.

18:42.310 --> 18:44.689
My friend Gretchen
makes me keep those out.

18:46.241 --> 18:48.448
She's a good egg.

18:50.379 --> 18:53.827
So, I-I hope it's okay
to ask, but...

18:53.862 --> 18:55.206
Sally.

18:55.241 --> 18:57.068
I-I imagine Lisa
would have told me,

18:57.103 --> 19:00.310
but I also know that any lead
has to be pretty substantial

19:00.344 --> 19:02.275
for my lawyer daughter
to share it.

19:02.310 --> 19:03.379
Yeah. No.

19:03.413 --> 19:06.103
No leads.
No. Still.

19:08.172 --> 19:09.758
But I haven't given up.

19:09.793 --> 19:12.448
I mean, of course not.

19:12.482 --> 19:16.344
There's always a chance that,
you know, that they'll --

19:16.379 --> 19:18.689
And...I mean, listen.

19:18.724 --> 19:21.586
You -- You got to look at -- You
got to look at Elizabeth Smart,

19:21.620 --> 19:23.482
Jaycee Dugard.

19:23.517 --> 19:27.241
There's -- There's a whole slew
of kids they've found.

19:27.275 --> 19:28.620
-So...
-Mm.

19:28.655 --> 19:30.793
...there's --
there's always a chance.

19:30.827 --> 19:33.793
Don't you think
that's a little naive?

19:34.793 --> 19:38.724
Um, no offense, Jack,
but...fuck you.

19:38.758 --> 19:39.827
Hey. Hey.

19:39.862 --> 19:41.758
I'm just trying to do you
a favor.

19:41.793 --> 19:43.448
-A favor?
-Well, you were the one

19:43.482 --> 19:46.172
who always said real friends
challenge each other,

19:46.206 --> 19:49.413
they don't let each other
off the hook.

19:49.448 --> 19:51.655
So...

19:51.689 --> 19:54.068
what do you need?

19:55.379 --> 19:57.655
I mean, after all this time...

19:59.586 --> 20:04.103
...what do you need to help you
feel whole again?

20:15.103 --> 20:17.275
[ Softly ]
Sorry.

20:17.310 --> 20:20.551
I could never feel whole again.

20:20.586 --> 20:22.344
Sorry.
Just --

20:22.379 --> 20:25.275
Like, even if she came home,

20:25.310 --> 20:28.620
I lost 20 years with her,
you know?

20:28.655 --> 20:30.103
And, I mean, please.

20:30.137 --> 20:32.448
I'm not stupid, okay?
I'm not dumb.

20:32.482 --> 20:35.689
I know she's probably nev--

20:38.689 --> 20:41.379
I just need to know...

20:42.379 --> 20:47.724
...that I did everything,
every single thing I could do

20:47.758 --> 20:49.448
to find her,
followed every lead,

20:49.482 --> 20:51.310
no matter how flimsy,
no matter how crazy --

20:51.344 --> 20:54.172
that I just did everything
I could to find her.

20:54.862 --> 20:59.310
And what would you do
if you found out that she was...

20:59.344 --> 21:01.413
[ Wind whistling ]

21:01.448 --> 21:04.068
...and you knew who it was?

21:04.103 --> 21:08.482
I-I mean, I'd call the police,
obviously.

21:08.517 --> 21:10.034
Call the police?

21:10.068 --> 21:13.413
What, just throw away
your golden opportunity?

21:13.448 --> 21:15.172
My golden opportunity?

21:15.206 --> 21:17.448
You wouldn't want to tie him up,
shoot him in the head?

21:17.482 --> 21:19.724
There it is. Okay. No.
Don't drag me into that.

21:19.758 --> 21:22.379
You can't tell me
that your justice fantasy

21:22.413 --> 21:24.275
-is turning the guy in.
-My justice fantasy?

21:24.310 --> 21:26.034
-Who...
-May-- Maybe you --

21:26.068 --> 21:29.827
you tap into that kind
of darkness and it helps you.

21:29.862 --> 21:31.551
-You know, it helps you --
-I don't want to go there.

21:31.586 --> 21:33.724
-Okay. All right.
-It doesn't help anything, okay?

21:33.758 --> 21:34.793
Okay. So --
All right.

21:34.827 --> 21:38.379
So if it's not revenge, what...

21:39.724 --> 21:42.413
...what would you want?

21:47.724 --> 21:50.034
I would want him to tell me
everything.

21:50.068 --> 21:51.724
-Mm-hmm.
-I would want him to tell me

21:51.758 --> 21:53.689
exactly what happened.

21:53.724 --> 21:55.517
-I would want to know every...
-Mm-hmm.

21:55.551 --> 21:57.517
...single detail.

21:57.551 --> 22:00.551
And then I would tell him
everything.

22:00.586 --> 22:03.448
I would tell him who he took,

22:03.482 --> 22:06.827
that she wasn't just some face
on a poster!

22:06.862 --> 22:09.034
Sure.
Yeah.

22:15.275 --> 22:18.344
But whatever it was,
whatever happened...

22:19.758 --> 22:24.172
...I...missed it.

22:24.206 --> 22:27.620
I...I should have protected her.

22:27.655 --> 22:32.448
But I didn't, because I...

22:32.482 --> 22:34.724
was drunk.

22:34.758 --> 22:37.482
You were always too hard
on yourself.

22:37.517 --> 22:39.137
No.

22:41.689 --> 22:43.379
You want a laugh?

22:43.413 --> 22:45.620
[ Laughs ]
Actually...

22:47.241 --> 22:50.206
...when you -- when you
rang my doorbell just now,

22:50.241 --> 22:53.620
um, I...

22:54.379 --> 22:56.551
...was about to chuck it all.

22:58.586 --> 23:01.034
Nineteen years of sobriety,
just --

23:01.068 --> 23:02.724
-Kkt!
-No.

23:02.758 --> 23:04.655
Yeah. Yeah.
Y-Yep.

23:04.689 --> 23:06.586
[ Sniffs ]
I have --

23:06.620 --> 23:09.275
I actually have a really good
bottle of vodka upstairs.

23:09.310 --> 23:11.344
[ Laughs ]

23:11.862 --> 23:15.758
But it's like 20 years...

23:16.379 --> 23:20.551
...of Christmases without her.

23:20.586 --> 23:23.379
It's just too fucking late.

23:25.551 --> 23:28.206
And then -- ding-dong.

23:28.241 --> 23:29.379
Here you are.

23:29.413 --> 23:31.379
Seriously?
That's...That's --

23:31.413 --> 23:33.103
Literary.

23:33.137 --> 23:35.172
Dickensian, even.

23:43.068 --> 23:44.551
Ay.

23:44.586 --> 23:46.827
[ Thunder rumbling ]

23:46.862 --> 23:49.551
[ Wind whistling ]

23:57.379 --> 23:59.206
Okay.

23:59.241 --> 24:02.551
Let's get you something sweet.

24:02.586 --> 24:05.137
-[ Kettle clangs ]
-More tea.

24:05.172 --> 24:07.275
[ Exhales sharply ]

24:07.310 --> 24:08.689
Hey.

24:08.724 --> 24:10.206
Don't be sad.

24:10.241 --> 24:13.379
-[ Laughs ]
-We have cookies and pie.

24:16.137 --> 24:17.413
Jack.

24:18.068 --> 24:20.068
Hey.
What's going on?

24:20.103 --> 24:21.448
Oh, Christmas.

24:21.482 --> 24:24.689
You know, it's supposed to be
so...simple,

24:24.724 --> 24:26.517
and I've made it so hard.

24:26.551 --> 24:28.206
No.
It's okay.

24:28.241 --> 24:30.689
Listen. Listen.
It's okay.

24:30.724 --> 24:36.034
Christmas is -- It's a magical
time for peacemaking.

24:36.068 --> 24:41.758
I just kept thinking, you know,
"I can fix all of this."

24:43.862 --> 24:46.448
And then you wake up one day
and you realize that,

24:46.482 --> 24:51.793
you know, for some things,
there are no do-overs, you know?

24:52.586 --> 24:54.620
But it's all right.

24:54.655 --> 24:56.379
It's all right.
You're here.

24:56.413 --> 24:59.586
And -- And the kids are gonna be
so happy to see you.

24:59.620 --> 25:01.517
And Julie -- Listen.
If you just --

25:01.551 --> 25:05.068
If you truly own up to
what you did and you apologize,

25:05.103 --> 25:08.137
then...I think people
will forgive --

25:08.172 --> 25:11.241
even -- even Julie.

25:11.275 --> 25:12.758
Okay?

25:13.758 --> 25:16.241
Hey.
It's gonna be okay.

25:16.275 --> 25:17.551
Come on.

25:19.068 --> 25:21.586
[ Exhales deeply ]

25:27.413 --> 25:28.517
Jack --

25:28.551 --> 25:32.241
I-I have missed you so much.

25:33.206 --> 25:36.310
It was always supposed to be
you and me, Darlene.

25:36.344 --> 25:39.068
But you know how much
I love you.

25:39.103 --> 25:42.206
You have to know that, right?

25:42.241 --> 25:45.206
Y-You can't tell me --

25:45.241 --> 25:47.482
You just can't tell me
that this --

25:47.517 --> 25:49.206
that this doesn't feel right.

25:51.206 --> 25:52.379
No.
I'm sorry.

25:54.379 --> 25:56.241
I'm sorry.

25:57.103 --> 25:59.655
[ Softly ]
I can't. I'm sorry. I can't.

26:01.310 --> 26:03.413
[ Thunder rumbling ]

26:04.448 --> 26:06.551
[ Mugs clanking ]

26:10.275 --> 26:11.724
Okay.

26:13.517 --> 26:14.793
Fine.

26:15.620 --> 26:18.241
[ Clears throat, sniffs ]

26:20.862 --> 26:22.310
Darlene?

26:22.344 --> 26:24.586
-Yeah?
-[ Clears throat ]

26:26.241 --> 26:28.241
I have to tell you something.

26:28.275 --> 26:30.103
Okay.

26:32.206 --> 26:34.448
It's about Sally.

26:40.551 --> 26:43.172
There's something
that I never told you.

26:43.206 --> 26:45.551
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

26:48.068 --> 26:49.758
What?

26:52.241 --> 26:54.413
What did you never tell me?

26:58.551 --> 27:00.137
Jack.

27:01.655 --> 27:04.103
What is this?

27:04.137 --> 27:06.275
What?

27:17.172 --> 27:19.551
[ Drawer closes ]

27:19.586 --> 27:21.689
[ Breathing shallowly ]

27:33.586 --> 27:35.620
[ Gasps ]

27:37.793 --> 27:39.620
I can't do this
with other people.

27:39.655 --> 27:42.482
It -- It has to be just us.

27:42.517 --> 27:44.241
Okay?

27:45.620 --> 27:50.344
Please...come -- come sit down.

27:51.758 --> 27:54.034
[ Music continues ]

27:58.517 --> 28:00.586
[ Exhales sharply ]

28:00.620 --> 28:03.793
[ Wind whistling ]

28:08.137 --> 28:10.137
Your...

28:10.172 --> 28:14.241
Your car didn't break down,
did it?

28:18.241 --> 28:21.724
And nobody knows you're...here.

28:24.379 --> 28:25.620
No.

28:31.379 --> 28:33.241
'Cause it was supposed to be
a surprise.

28:33.275 --> 28:35.172
I get how this looks,

28:35.206 --> 28:37.620
but I had to be sure
that we could be alone

28:37.655 --> 28:39.724
so that we could work
through this.

28:39.758 --> 28:44.344
I just -- I...I couldn't
figure out another way.

28:44.862 --> 28:48.344
Darlene, I don't want to
have to use these,

28:48.379 --> 28:53.482
so please, please, please
just...sit down,

28:53.517 --> 28:55.206
and we can talk.

28:55.241 --> 28:57.206
No, I won't.

28:57.241 --> 29:01.103
When I saw that interview
you did,

29:01.137 --> 29:05.034
it was like you were speaking
directly to me.

29:05.068 --> 29:09.551
And I knew then that you deserve
to know the truth.

29:09.586 --> 29:12.620
[ Music continues ]

29:13.241 --> 29:15.344
[ Voice breaking ]
Where is she?

29:19.620 --> 29:21.034
She's gone, Dar.

29:24.517 --> 29:26.000
Gone?

29:27.620 --> 29:29.344
You mean d--

29:30.862 --> 29:32.379
You mean dead?

29:32.413 --> 29:35.689
[ Music builds, continues ]

29:35.724 --> 29:38.344
No. No.

29:38.379 --> 29:40.068
No.

29:40.103 --> 29:42.241
[ Exhales deeply ]
No.

29:42.275 --> 29:44.310
No. No.

29:44.344 --> 29:45.724
No!

29:45.758 --> 29:47.793
[ Breathing heavily ]

29:47.827 --> 29:50.137
Darlene, please.

29:50.172 --> 29:51.758
Just breathe.

29:51.793 --> 29:53.310
Just breathe, okay?

29:53.344 --> 29:55.275
Just take d--
some deep breaths.

29:55.310 --> 29:56.827
Just...

29:56.862 --> 29:59.724
[ Music fades ]

29:59.758 --> 30:01.793
[ Birds chirping ]

30:01.827 --> 30:05.206
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

30:14.724 --> 30:17.793
DARLENE:
[ Sobbing ] Oh, no.

30:17.827 --> 30:19.310
No!

30:19.344 --> 30:21.655
-[ Kettle whistling ]
-JACK: Will you please --

30:21.689 --> 30:24.689
Just breathe.
Take some deep breaths, okay?

30:24.724 --> 30:26.275
-No. My baby.
-Okay -- Okay, Darlene.

30:26.310 --> 30:27.689
-Listen to me. Listen to me.
-My baby. No.

30:27.724 --> 30:30.310
-Shh. Shh. Shh. Shh.
-No. No. My baby.

30:30.344 --> 30:32.482
Listen to me, okay?
Come with me.

30:32.517 --> 30:34.448
Come with me.
We're gonna go sit down.

30:34.482 --> 30:37.310
-[ Sobbing, mumbling ]
-We're gonna go sit down, okay?

30:37.344 --> 30:40.827
Come on. I got you.
I got you.

30:40.862 --> 30:43.310
All right. There you go.
There you go.

30:43.344 --> 30:45.310
[ Gasps ]
No.

30:45.344 --> 30:46.689
No.

30:46.724 --> 30:49.655
[ Thunder rumbling,
whistling continues ]

30:51.517 --> 30:54.482
[ Kettle clanks,
whistling slows, stops ]

30:59.206 --> 31:02.172
[ Liquid pouring,
kettle clanks ]

31:32.103 --> 31:34.689
So, how much...
do you want to know?

31:34.724 --> 31:38.586
I mean, I'm -- I'm --
I'm not sure what's helpful.

31:41.517 --> 31:44.310
Tell me everything.
Everything.

31:44.344 --> 31:45.517
Tell me.

31:45.551 --> 31:47.172
Okay.

31:47.206 --> 31:48.655
Okay.

31:49.655 --> 31:52.206
So, here it is.
Um...[ Clears throat ]

31:52.241 --> 31:55.482
That day, uh,
I was driving from a work site,

31:55.517 --> 32:00.344
and, uh, I saw Sally walking
home from the high school.

32:01.068 --> 32:02.793
S-She seemed upset.

32:02.827 --> 32:05.275
There -- There was no one else
on the street,

32:05.310 --> 32:09.586
so I, uh, pulled up beside her
and...startled her.

32:09.620 --> 32:13.241
But once she saw it was me,
she...she relaxed,

32:13.275 --> 32:16.758
and, um...
she asked me for a ride.

32:16.793 --> 32:18.275
I said yes, of course.

32:18.310 --> 32:21.310
And, uh, s--
And she got in.

32:25.137 --> 32:29.310
Anyway, um, I suggested
that we drive out

32:29.344 --> 32:30.689
to that spot on the lake.

32:30.724 --> 32:33.000
They dragged the lake.

32:35.310 --> 32:37.517
She's not in the lake.

32:41.241 --> 32:43.793
So, on -- So, on the drive over,
I could tell, you know,

32:43.827 --> 32:46.310
that she was really upset.

32:46.827 --> 32:48.586
So when we got to the lake,

32:48.620 --> 32:51.655
I, uh, I took out a blanket,
and I laid it on the grass.

32:51.689 --> 32:57.793
And we sat down, and she starts
talking about you.

32:58.551 --> 32:59.517
Me?

32:59.551 --> 33:01.379
She was worried about you.

33:01.413 --> 33:05.655
She'd found you on the bathroom
floor the night before.

33:07.103 --> 33:10.827
We were talking about how
worried we both were about you,

33:10.862 --> 33:15.206
and, uh...she started to cry.

33:15.241 --> 33:17.724
So I just -- I instinctually --
I just --

33:17.758 --> 33:19.172
I hugged her, you know?

33:19.206 --> 33:22.482
Because we --
we were always so close.

33:26.275 --> 33:29.689
B-But this was...

33:29.724 --> 33:31.793
[ Thunder rumbling ]

33:31.827 --> 33:35.241
And she was looking up at me,
and, uh...

33:35.275 --> 33:39.448
and she looked so much like you,
you know?

33:40.689 --> 33:44.068
And then, all of a sudden,
we were kissing.

33:44.103 --> 33:46.206
-[ Gasps ]
-Aah! [ Groans ]

33:46.241 --> 33:48.103
[ Dramatic music plays ]

33:50.620 --> 33:52.137
[ Breathing heavily ]

33:58.448 --> 34:00.620
[ Latch clicks ]

34:05.655 --> 34:07.172
[ Grunts ]

34:07.206 --> 34:10.482
[ Music continues ]

34:10.517 --> 34:13.482
[ Gasps, groans ]

34:13.517 --> 34:16.068
[ Grunting ]

34:21.793 --> 34:25.068
[ Breathing heavily ]

34:31.586 --> 34:34.172
[ Groans ]

34:34.827 --> 34:36.689
[ Window rattles ]

34:43.379 --> 34:46.448
[ Groans, breathing heavily ]

34:53.344 --> 34:55.137
[ Footsteps approaching ]

34:55.172 --> 34:57.655
JACK:
Darlene?

34:57.689 --> 35:00.241
Can't we just talk?

35:04.310 --> 35:06.482
Listen.
I...

35:06.517 --> 35:09.344
I know how much
you need to know everything,

35:09.379 --> 35:13.310
and...I'm here to do that.

35:16.068 --> 35:18.448
You deserve the truth.

35:20.551 --> 35:27.000
I deserved the truth...
20 years ago!

35:38.758 --> 35:40.413
Okay.

35:42.689 --> 35:45.172
You want to tell me the truth?

35:47.862 --> 35:49.620
Go ahead.

35:50.724 --> 35:52.517
I'm listening.

35:53.517 --> 35:56.379
Not through a door.

35:56.413 --> 35:58.344
Please.
Come on.

36:00.517 --> 36:04.344
Darlene, I-I didn't come here
to hurt you.

36:05.344 --> 36:07.724
I...

36:07.758 --> 36:13.586
I need to tell you as --
as much as you need to hear it.

36:15.068 --> 36:18.068
Please, can't we just sit down
and -- and talk

36:18.103 --> 36:19.482
like -- like human beings?

36:19.517 --> 36:22.517
It's -- It's just me.
It's still me!

36:24.344 --> 36:26.000
It's Jack.

36:28.724 --> 36:30.172
Please?

36:30.206 --> 36:32.482
[ Wind whistling ]

36:35.620 --> 36:37.172
Okay.

36:38.758 --> 36:43.275
But I want you to back up
five steps,

36:43.310 --> 36:46.206
and I want to hear you
count them off!

36:46.241 --> 36:48.758
All right.

36:48.793 --> 36:55.137
One, two, three, four, five.

36:57.379 --> 36:59.034
Okay.

37:05.241 --> 37:06.586
Okay.

37:16.586 --> 37:20.310
You really burned the shit
out of my neck.

37:20.344 --> 37:22.379
[ Clears throat ]

37:22.413 --> 37:25.137
I just meant, you know,
well done.

37:27.482 --> 37:30.103
-Are you complimenting me?
-Well, it was a smart move.

37:30.137 --> 37:31.551
You -- You were always
very smart.

37:31.586 --> 37:33.137
That's why I've had to do
all of this.

37:33.172 --> 37:35.034
I know how smart you are.

37:35.068 --> 37:36.310
Okay.
So, look.

37:36.344 --> 37:40.275
Please. Please don't --
don't freak out.

37:40.310 --> 37:43.137
This...This is just
for my protection, okay?

37:43.172 --> 37:44.586
-Jesus.
-I know. I know.

37:44.620 --> 37:47.206
I know.
I know.

37:47.241 --> 37:49.275
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

37:50.172 --> 37:54.655
How about I-I-I put it away
when we sit down?

37:54.689 --> 37:55.724
Deal?

37:57.172 --> 38:01.586
And, um...you can get rid
of that.

38:07.379 --> 38:09.413
[ Razor clatters ]

38:09.448 --> 38:11.689
[ Music continues ]

38:21.137 --> 38:23.241
[ Wind whistling ]

38:30.655 --> 38:33.310
Right. Right.
Of course.

38:38.241 --> 38:40.344
[ Exhales deeply ]

38:43.103 --> 38:46.137
It wasn't some insidious plan.

38:46.172 --> 38:47.551
I need you to know that.

38:47.586 --> 38:50.482
My daughter didn't kiss you.

38:50.517 --> 38:51.827
It's the truth, Darlene.

38:51.862 --> 38:53.758
It may not be
what you want to hear.

38:53.793 --> 38:56.206
Don't give me that.

38:58.551 --> 39:03.206
Your view of her...
was so skewed.

39:03.724 --> 39:06.793
I don't think you realize how
cut off she felt from you both.

39:09.448 --> 39:11.689
I mean, in your eyes,
she was still a child.

39:11.724 --> 39:13.344
But she was 16.

39:13.379 --> 39:15.689
Sixteen isa child.

39:15.724 --> 39:17.827
It's not the same thing,
and you know it.

39:17.862 --> 39:19.793
Fuck you.

39:24.586 --> 39:26.275
Okay.

39:26.310 --> 39:28.758
Do you want me to continue?

39:33.517 --> 39:35.482
-[ Gasps ]
-[ Sighs ]

39:35.517 --> 39:38.000
[ Music continues ]

39:42.137 --> 39:45.620
It -- It all happened so fast.

39:46.620 --> 39:48.344
You know, it all felt so smooth,

39:48.379 --> 39:50.827
and then, suddenly,
she was screaming.

39:50.862 --> 39:53.655
So I-I put my hand
over her mouth.

39:53.689 --> 39:55.620
I was scared somebody
would hear,

39:55.655 --> 39:57.793
so I kept telling her
to calm down,

39:57.827 --> 39:59.620
that we just needed to
talk it out,

39:59.655 --> 40:01.827
you know, that maybe we --
we could keep it to ourselves.

40:01.862 --> 40:05.103
-Keep it between yourselves?
-I-I don't know. She j-- I --

40:05.137 --> 40:06.586
She wouldn't stop screaming.
I could think.

40:06.620 --> 40:08.448
-What did you expect her to do?!
-I don't know!

40:08.482 --> 40:11.724
I-I just needed a minute,
just one fucking minute.

40:11.758 --> 40:13.344
But she -- she wouldn't stop,

40:13.379 --> 40:16.827
so I-I-I pushed harder,
and...

40:16.862 --> 40:20.517
Her neck...was broken.

40:20.551 --> 40:22.655
It was an accident.

40:22.689 --> 40:24.724
DARLENE:
[ Whimpers ]

40:32.827 --> 40:35.241
[ Thunder rumbling ]

40:38.620 --> 40:40.758
I kept her French book.

40:44.448 --> 40:46.689
She'd written and drawn
on the brown-bag cover --

40:46.724 --> 40:48.620
you know, "Je'taime,"
"Oui, oui,"

40:48.655 --> 40:52.068
"La musique, c'est la vie,"
and her name inside.

40:53.517 --> 40:55.241
Do you still have it?

40:55.275 --> 40:56.344
Yeah.

40:57.482 --> 40:58.620
It's out in my truck.

40:58.655 --> 41:00.551
I want to see it.

41:01.517 --> 41:03.724
-If you're sure.
-I'm sure.

41:03.758 --> 41:05.241
Sure.

41:06.517 --> 41:09.068
[ Thunder rumbling ]

41:10.379 --> 41:13.000
[ Music continues ]

41:15.551 --> 41:18.172
[ Breathing heavily ]

41:24.103 --> 41:25.344
[ Door closes ]

41:25.379 --> 41:28.172
[ Gasping ]

41:29.103 --> 41:32.310
[ Grunting ]

41:34.655 --> 41:36.758
[ Wind whistling ]

41:38.586 --> 41:40.413
[ Exhales deeply ]

41:40.448 --> 41:42.068
Oh, God.

41:57.137 --> 41:59.172
[ Music builds, continues ]

42:19.103 --> 42:21.275
[ Grunting ]

42:24.517 --> 42:26.103
Gretchen!

42:26.137 --> 42:28.586
Gretchen!
Gretchen!

42:28.620 --> 42:31.758
Help!
Gretchen!

42:31.793 --> 42:34.241
Help!
Help me!

42:34.275 --> 42:36.344
Help me!

42:39.344 --> 42:40.689
JACK:
Calm down.

42:40.724 --> 42:42.586
-[ Grunting ]
-Darlene. Darlene. Darlene.

42:42.620 --> 42:44.172
-No. No.
-Shh, shh, shh.

42:44.206 --> 42:46.275
Calm down.
Calm down!

42:46.310 --> 42:47.586
Shh.

42:47.620 --> 42:50.172
[ Breathing heavily ]

43:27.724 --> 43:29.310
Why would...

43:31.448 --> 43:33.482
Why...

43:34.413 --> 43:36.482
Why would you...

43:36.517 --> 43:38.827
Why would you keep this?

43:38.862 --> 43:41.413
Why?
[ Breathing heavily ]

43:41.448 --> 43:43.310
I don't know.

43:43.344 --> 43:45.655
[ Exhales sharply ]

43:45.689 --> 43:50.068
Now I understand
why you were the only one

43:50.103 --> 43:54.551
who didn't keep telling me,
"Have hope, Darlene."

43:54.586 --> 43:58.000
"Keep up the --
the faith, Darlene."

44:00.448 --> 44:02.275
You see why I had to leave?

44:02.310 --> 44:04.379
'Cause you couldn't lie
to my face anymore?

44:04.413 --> 44:06.758
Have you any idea
how hard it was

44:06.793 --> 44:09.758
to keep that nightmare inside
and not let it show?

44:09.793 --> 44:13.689
I mean, we should have been
grieving together.

44:13.724 --> 44:15.172
Oh, my...

44:15.206 --> 44:17.724
Did you --
Did you just roll your eyes?

44:19.103 --> 44:21.448
You think I don't care?

44:22.310 --> 44:25.586
I-I got into this hell
because I cared.

44:25.620 --> 44:28.137
Sally was in serious pain,

44:28.172 --> 44:30.517
and I was the one
who was there for her.

44:30.551 --> 44:34.793
I never meant for any of that
to happen.

44:34.827 --> 44:37.206
-It was an accident.
-No.

44:38.310 --> 44:41.758
She was 16,
and you were an adult.

44:41.793 --> 44:44.620
She was your niece.
She trusted you.

44:45.241 --> 44:47.413
And you took advantage of that.

44:47.448 --> 44:53.310
You took her to an isolated
place, and you broke her neck.

44:55.517 --> 44:57.655
And then you just went away.

44:58.586 --> 45:01.068
Just went off
to start a whole new life,

45:01.103 --> 45:04.620
and left me and Ed here,
living in this nightmare

45:04.655 --> 45:06.827
that you created.

45:06.862 --> 45:09.379
None of it was an accident!

45:09.413 --> 45:12.827
Those were all choices
that you made.

45:12.862 --> 45:15.758
Shouldn't you --
Shouldn't you, of all people,

45:15.793 --> 45:17.793
understand mistakes?!

45:17.827 --> 45:20.034
I mean, what was I
supposed to do?

45:20.068 --> 45:23.482
My -- My whole life,
my family's lives

45:23.517 --> 45:24.586
would have been ruined!

45:24.620 --> 45:25.689
What about Sally's life?

45:25.724 --> 45:27.344
It wouldn't have
brought her back!

45:27.379 --> 45:29.103
Jack, please.

45:29.137 --> 45:33.344
You come back here to -- Why?
Why? Why?

45:33.379 --> 45:36.103
To hold me hostage
in my own house

45:36.137 --> 45:38.068
to just unburden yourself?

45:38.103 --> 45:42.068
I am putting myself through
all of this for you,

45:42.103 --> 45:43.413
and you don't even care!

45:43.448 --> 45:45.068
No, I don't care.

45:45.103 --> 45:46.655
-I fucking hate you!
-Well, you know what?

45:46.689 --> 45:49.379
I fucking hate myself too!

45:49.413 --> 45:51.724
[ Thunder rumbling,
wind whistling ]

45:51.758 --> 45:54.379
[ Both breathing heavily ]

46:14.068 --> 46:15.724
So now what?

46:16.758 --> 46:18.689
Well, you know what?

46:19.758 --> 46:26.034
I think this is a decision
that we need to make together.

46:28.827 --> 46:31.379
-You're serious?
-I am.

46:31.413 --> 46:35.034
I mean, this -- this is, um...

46:35.068 --> 46:39.068
It's...uncharted territory.

46:41.586 --> 46:43.344
[ Chuckles softly ]

46:56.310 --> 46:59.586
Do you --
Do you want to go change?

47:00.448 --> 47:02.103
You're freezing.

47:07.827 --> 47:09.310
Yeah.

47:09.344 --> 47:11.793
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

47:13.206 --> 47:15.482
[ Wind whistling ]

47:56.724 --> 47:58.758
[ Music continues ]

48:15.689 --> 48:17.206
DARLENE:
[ Gasps, grunts ]

48:17.241 --> 48:19.206
-[ Glass breaking ]
-JACK: Aah! [ Groans ]

48:19.241 --> 48:22.275
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

48:22.310 --> 48:24.724
[ Gunshot ]

48:24.758 --> 48:26.586
JACK:
Fuck me!

48:26.620 --> 48:29.379
[ Breathing heavily ]

48:33.137 --> 48:34.827
Who are you kidding, Jack?

48:34.862 --> 48:38.758
We're not making
any mutual decisions.

48:38.793 --> 48:41.000
Stand up.

48:44.551 --> 48:46.275
Go.

48:48.413 --> 48:50.655
[ Wind whistling ]

48:52.137 --> 48:54.137
This door right here.
Right here.

48:54.172 --> 48:55.517
Open it.

48:55.551 --> 48:57.137
[ Hinges squeaking ]

48:57.172 --> 48:58.827
Open it.

48:58.862 --> 49:00.551
Okay.
Go. Down.

49:00.586 --> 49:03.275
Keep your hands where
I can see them.

49:03.310 --> 49:05.068
All the way down.

49:13.655 --> 49:15.344
[ Grunts ]

49:15.379 --> 49:17.551
[ Breathing heavily ]

49:41.206 --> 49:43.310
Look at all of this.

49:44.482 --> 49:45.793
Hey!

49:47.793 --> 49:50.344
Look at it.

49:50.379 --> 49:51.827
Look at her.

49:51.862 --> 49:56.310
All the fliers,
all the headlines.

49:56.344 --> 49:59.586
"No trace of Sally Hagen."

50:03.172 --> 50:05.517
Where is my daughter buried?

50:12.586 --> 50:15.379
I guess you're all talked out
now.

50:26.862 --> 50:31.586
I kept every single one
of her -- her things.

50:32.655 --> 50:35.137
Just in case.

50:36.827 --> 50:39.103
In case someday...

50:41.724 --> 50:43.586
...she came home.

50:43.620 --> 50:45.172
[ Lid clicks ]

50:45.206 --> 50:47.724
Probably seems pathetic to you,
doesn't it?

50:47.758 --> 50:49.275
No.

50:51.482 --> 50:53.068
Seems human.

50:58.172 --> 50:59.379
You know what?

51:01.482 --> 51:03.310
God.
Even in my --

51:03.344 --> 51:05.827
Even in my most
paranoid moments,

51:05.862 --> 51:08.241
even when I was just crazed

51:08.275 --> 51:12.172
and I looked at everyone around
me like they were a suspect,

51:12.206 --> 51:16.586
I barely --
I barely ever landed on you.

51:17.344 --> 51:20.275
And you had a rock-solid alibi.

51:20.310 --> 51:25.655
How in the world
did you manage that?

51:25.689 --> 51:27.172
Oh.
[ Clears throat ]

51:27.793 --> 51:30.103
By the time they got around
to checking my alibi

51:30.137 --> 51:35.068
with the guys on the crew,
it was...it was a week later.

51:35.793 --> 51:40.068
Patrick said he knew I was
still there until after 5:00

51:40.103 --> 51:42.586
because that was the day

51:42.620 --> 51:45.275
I brought him a Snickers
and a Coke.

51:45.862 --> 51:48.620
So dear old Patrick lied
for you?

51:48.655 --> 51:50.517
No.
No.

51:52.172 --> 51:54.724
I brought him a Snickers
and a Coke the day before.

51:57.275 --> 52:00.172
It was just an honest mistake.

52:01.758 --> 52:04.517
Cops just weren't that thorough.

52:04.551 --> 52:06.448
[ Chuckles softly ]

52:06.482 --> 52:09.068
-No shit.
-Mm.

52:10.344 --> 52:16.241
And you were a churchgoing
family man, so...

52:20.137 --> 52:22.689
Oh, God.
I imagined.

52:23.655 --> 52:27.551
I imagined so many things.

52:29.275 --> 52:30.586
Oh.

52:30.620 --> 52:34.034
Maybe she...
Maybe she had been kidnapped

52:34.068 --> 52:36.517
and -- and she was being
held somewhere.

52:36.551 --> 52:40.448
Or maybe she'd been sold
into s--

52:40.482 --> 52:44.448
Or maybe she'd -- she'd managed
to escape whoever --

52:44.482 --> 52:46.448
whoever took her, but she --
Maybe --

52:46.482 --> 52:48.413
Maybe she couldn't remember
who she was.

52:48.448 --> 52:51.275
Or -- Or maybe --
maybe the police were right.

52:51.310 --> 52:52.482
Maybe they were right.

52:52.517 --> 52:55.310
Maybe she did run away from me.

52:55.344 --> 52:59.517
The years, the wondering,
the time, the effort,

52:59.551 --> 53:03.172
the energy, the website
and paperwork

53:03.206 --> 53:05.758
and -- and -- and --
and the phone calls!

53:05.793 --> 53:07.655
The...

53:07.689 --> 53:09.551
[ Dramatic music plays ]

53:09.586 --> 53:11.000
The phone calls.

53:11.620 --> 53:15.620
I recorded every
single one of them

53:15.655 --> 53:17.586
until the damn thing broke.

53:17.620 --> 53:19.689
[ Breathing heavily ]

53:19.724 --> 53:23.724
People calling me at all hours
of the day and night,

53:23.758 --> 53:25.379
waking me up
in the middle of the night

53:25.413 --> 53:28.689
to tell me about some --
some dream they'd had.

53:28.724 --> 53:31.241
Or sometimes they were
a psychic,

53:31.275 --> 53:36.310
and they'd tell me the most
awful, gruesome, gory details.

53:36.344 --> 53:41.275
All those fucking years,
listening to these calls,

53:41.310 --> 53:43.413
trying to find some little tip,

53:43.448 --> 53:46.482
somethingthat would give me
an answer.

53:46.517 --> 53:51.482
And the whole time --
the whole time -- it was you!

53:51.517 --> 53:54.068
It was just you!

53:54.103 --> 53:57.137
It was you!

53:57.172 --> 53:59.034
[ Music continues ]

53:59.068 --> 54:00.586
You.

54:08.482 --> 54:10.586
Do you remember this?

54:11.655 --> 54:13.482
Yeah.

54:13.517 --> 54:16.275
[ Breathing heavily ]
Yeah.

54:17.655 --> 54:21.068
She wrote songs
almost every day.

54:21.103 --> 54:23.517
[ Chuckles ]
God.

54:23.551 --> 54:25.793
She would just race home
from school

54:25.827 --> 54:27.620
and s-shut her bedroom door.

54:27.655 --> 54:31.172
And I'd -- I'd tiptoe over,
and I'd --

54:31.206 --> 54:34.103
I'd listen to her singing.

54:35.379 --> 54:37.517
And she never thought
she was any good.

54:37.551 --> 54:39.448
But she was so good.

54:39.482 --> 54:42.517
Oh, my God.
She was so good.

54:42.551 --> 54:44.448
She didn't think so,

54:44.482 --> 54:47.620
so she never...
she never kept any of them.

54:47.655 --> 54:49.241
She just recorded.

54:49.827 --> 54:52.620
She recorded over and over
and over again

54:52.655 --> 54:54.689
on this -- this one tape.

54:54.724 --> 54:57.310
Just this one tape.
It's what I...

54:58.620 --> 55:00.586
It's what I have.

55:01.448 --> 55:03.068
[ Chuckles softly ]

55:03.103 --> 55:07.517
This is the last song
she recorded before you...

55:11.379 --> 55:13.275
You failed her.

55:14.413 --> 55:16.413
[ Button clicks ]

55:16.448 --> 55:22.551
SALLY:
♪ Hold me closer♪

55:24.241 --> 55:29.517
♪ Hold my hand
a little tighter♪

55:30.689 --> 55:32.586
♪ Don't let me go♪

55:32.620 --> 55:35.379
♪ Let me just foll--♪

55:35.413 --> 55:37.517
[ Button clicks ]

55:38.724 --> 55:40.827
God.
She loved music.

55:40.862 --> 55:43.103
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

55:43.137 --> 55:45.586
I'm sure you remember that.

55:47.172 --> 55:51.034
After all, she was your niece.

55:51.413 --> 55:54.482
You knew her since she was born.

55:58.482 --> 56:01.517
Lisa wasn't just Sally's cousin.

56:01.551 --> 56:04.517
She was Sally's best friend.

56:05.448 --> 56:11.275
You took your daughter's
best friend away from her.

56:13.724 --> 56:16.000
[ Music continues ]

56:25.379 --> 56:27.482
[ Shovel clangs ]

56:33.517 --> 56:36.068
You asked if I had
a revenge fantasy.

56:36.103 --> 56:37.551
Remember?

56:39.172 --> 56:40.448
Well, I lied.

56:42.103 --> 56:47.344
I fantasized all the time
about bringing him down here,

56:47.379 --> 56:50.448
about ripping him apart.

56:50.482 --> 56:52.793
Darlene, I am so...

56:52.827 --> 56:54.793
-[ shovel clangs ]
-...so --

56:54.827 --> 56:56.413
-[ Grunts ]
-[ Groans ]

56:56.448 --> 56:59.000
[ Wind whistling ]

57:04.379 --> 57:06.344
Come on, Coley.

57:06.379 --> 57:10.551
You begged me to go out again.
What are we doing?

57:10.586 --> 57:12.344
What are we doing?
You appear to be loitering.

57:12.379 --> 57:14.517
Come on.

57:18.655 --> 57:19.724
[ Grunts ]

57:19.758 --> 57:22.034
Ow!
Shit.

57:22.068 --> 57:23.275
Fuck.

57:23.310 --> 57:25.689
-Aah!
-Oh, God.

57:25.724 --> 57:27.724
Oh, shit.
[ Breathing heavily ]

57:27.758 --> 57:31.103
[ Exhales deeply, groans ]

57:31.551 --> 57:33.379
Yeah.

57:34.275 --> 57:36.551
It w-- It was an accident.

57:36.586 --> 57:39.241
DARLENE:
Don't...

57:39.275 --> 57:41.413
Don't you dare.
Don't you...

57:41.448 --> 57:46.034
Don't you ever...
say that to me...

57:46.068 --> 57:48.172
again.

57:48.206 --> 57:49.689
Don't.

57:52.793 --> 57:55.103
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

58:13.689 --> 58:15.310
Wait.

58:16.827 --> 58:19.068
-What are you doing?
-I don't know.

58:19.103 --> 58:21.793
Where...Where are you going?

58:23.344 --> 58:25.275
-I don't know.
-Darlene.

58:25.310 --> 58:27.310
Darlene, it --

58:27.344 --> 58:29.448
Darlene, don't --
don't leave me down here.

58:29.482 --> 58:31.172
Ple-- Please.
Dar--Darlene.

58:31.206 --> 58:32.827
Don't leave me on my --
on my own down here.

58:32.862 --> 58:35.137
Please, Darlene.
Please. Ple--

58:35.172 --> 58:37.206
[ Hinges squeaking,
door closes ]

58:37.241 --> 58:39.689
[ Breathing heavily, mumbling ]

58:46.689 --> 58:48.413
No.
Darlene, ple-- ple--

58:48.448 --> 58:50.068
Please, Darlene!
Darlene!

58:50.103 --> 58:51.482
I have panic attacks!

58:51.517 --> 58:55.137
For real!
For fucking real!

58:55.172 --> 58:57.724
[ Wheezes ]

59:03.103 --> 59:05.068
[ Footsteps approaching ]

59:05.103 --> 59:07.137
-[ Door opens ]
-Oh, thank God.

59:07.172 --> 59:09.137
-[ Door closes ]
-Thank God.

59:09.172 --> 59:11.448
-[ Wood creaking ]
-[ Sobs ]

59:14.172 --> 59:17.137
Th-- Thank you.

59:17.172 --> 59:18.413
[ Exhales deeply ]

59:18.448 --> 59:20.275
Thank you.
Thank you.

59:21.379 --> 59:23.448
Thank you.

59:23.482 --> 59:29.103
It's not fun to scream
and scream

59:29.137 --> 59:31.275
and not be heard, is it?

59:34.448 --> 59:37.482
I started having panic attacks
soon after.

59:39.586 --> 59:43.103
I'd never had anything
like that before.

59:43.137 --> 59:45.103
You know, a man's supposed to be
the pillar of strength,

59:45.137 --> 59:49.172
you know, keeps his --
keeps his feelings to himself.

59:49.206 --> 59:52.655
Does what's necessary
for his family, you know?

59:54.448 --> 59:58.413
But even then, you know, back
then, I was starting to crack.

59:58.448 --> 1:00:00.241
I mean, you know
what it was like with Julie.

1:00:00.275 --> 1:00:01.344
You know your sister.

1:00:02.344 --> 1:00:05.137
I wasn't trusted with anything
in my house

1:00:05.172 --> 1:00:06.827
except bringing in the money.

1:00:06.862 --> 1:00:08.413
[ Chuckles ]

1:00:08.448 --> 1:00:10.827
I felt...

1:00:10.862 --> 1:00:13.137
I felt irrelevant.

1:00:13.172 --> 1:00:14.517
Oh, right.

1:00:14.551 --> 1:00:18.172
Because it's everybody else's
fault, isn't it?

1:00:18.206 --> 1:00:22.586
Everybody else is responsible
for what youdid.

1:00:22.620 --> 1:00:25.275
Me, Julie, your dad.

1:00:25.310 --> 1:00:26.793
How about Sally?

1:00:26.827 --> 1:00:29.034
Is Sally also at fault?

1:00:29.068 --> 1:00:32.137
Is it also Sally's fault?

1:00:32.172 --> 1:00:33.517
Is it?

1:00:33.551 --> 1:00:36.172
It -- It may seem twisted
and impossible to you...

1:00:36.206 --> 1:00:37.517
-Shut up.
-...but I loved you then,

1:00:37.551 --> 1:00:40.103
-and I love you know.
-Shut the fuck up!

1:00:40.137 --> 1:00:41.724
[ Gunshot, dog barking ]

1:00:41.758 --> 1:00:44.206
[ Wind whistling ]

1:00:46.103 --> 1:00:48.827
[ Gasps ]

1:00:48.862 --> 1:00:50.758
[ Breathing heavily ]
Whoa!

1:00:50.793 --> 1:00:52.655
-Whoa!
-[ Laughing ]

1:00:52.689 --> 1:00:55.827
Oh, my God.
I shot you!

1:00:55.862 --> 1:00:58.413
Oh, yeah, baby.

1:00:58.448 --> 1:01:00.724
That's the drunk
I knew and loved.

1:01:00.758 --> 1:01:02.310
Huh?

1:01:02.344 --> 1:01:04.482
DARLENE: Hello.
This is Darlene Hagen,

1:01:04.517 --> 1:01:07.551
and you've reached my
very serious voicemail message.

1:01:07.586 --> 1:01:09.413
Thank you and farewell.

1:01:09.448 --> 1:01:11.482
-[ Beep ]
-Hey. Hey. It's me.

1:01:11.517 --> 1:01:16.448
Did you just hear a gunshot
or...thunder or something?

1:01:16.482 --> 1:01:17.793
Is your power out too?

1:01:18.793 --> 1:01:20.241
-Are you sleeping?
-[ Dog yelps ]

1:01:20.275 --> 1:01:22.137
Are you asleep?

1:01:22.172 --> 1:01:24.586
Are you ignoring me,
you beautiful bitch?

1:01:24.620 --> 1:01:26.517
I'm sorry. I know you don't like
when I call you that,

1:01:26.551 --> 1:01:28.241
even though it's
just a reappropriated term

1:01:28.275 --> 1:01:29.758
of endearment --
although, to your point,

1:01:29.793 --> 1:01:33.103
can you reappropriate a word
laden with such -- click!

1:01:33.137 --> 1:01:35.310
[ Cellphone beeps ]

1:01:35.344 --> 1:01:38.103
Do I go over there?
Am I being overbearing?

1:01:38.137 --> 1:01:39.448
I'm gonna call the landline.

1:01:39.482 --> 1:01:40.758
We're calling the landline,
Coley.

1:01:42.586 --> 1:01:45.413
[ Pulsating tone ]

1:01:45.448 --> 1:01:46.689
That's odd.

1:01:47.586 --> 1:01:50.482
You have pooped,
and we are going in.

1:01:50.517 --> 1:01:52.206
Coley, come on.

1:01:52.241 --> 1:01:54.413
Come on.
Let's get you warm.

1:01:55.724 --> 1:01:59.310
[ Wind whistling ]

1:01:59.344 --> 1:02:01.620
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

1:02:01.655 --> 1:02:04.586
JACK:
[ Breathing heavily ] Okay.

1:02:04.620 --> 1:02:06.275
Okay.

1:02:09.517 --> 1:02:12.034
Okay.
I'm ready.

1:02:12.068 --> 1:02:14.172
[ Inhales deeply ]

1:02:16.448 --> 1:02:18.137
Wait a minute.

1:02:19.793 --> 1:02:21.206
Wait a minute.

1:02:31.206 --> 1:02:34.758
You wantme...to kill you?

1:02:41.689 --> 1:02:44.034
Well, don't you want to?

1:02:49.103 --> 1:02:50.655
No.

1:02:52.310 --> 1:02:54.344
Actually...

1:02:55.103 --> 1:02:56.206
...no.

1:02:56.241 --> 1:02:59.793
Of course you do.
Of course you do.

1:02:59.827 --> 1:03:01.620
-Oh, God.
-You want revenge,

1:03:01.655 --> 1:03:03.482
and I don't want to survive
the night.

1:03:03.517 --> 1:03:05.689
Stop telling me what I want.

1:03:05.724 --> 1:03:09.724
And I don't care what you want.

1:03:09.758 --> 1:03:14.137
You haven't taken one
fucking ounce of accountability.

1:03:14.172 --> 1:03:16.655
You want me to kill you?

1:03:17.379 --> 1:03:20.000
You're not making me do that.

1:03:23.310 --> 1:03:26.275
So, Jack...

1:03:26.724 --> 1:03:31.103
...I guess we're back
to the mutual decision.

1:03:31.137 --> 1:03:35.655
I say let's come up with
another plan.

1:03:42.275 --> 1:03:44.413
-Okay.
-[ Wood creaking ]

1:03:44.448 --> 1:03:45.793
[ Grunts ]

1:03:45.827 --> 1:03:47.172
[ Gasps ]

1:03:47.206 --> 1:03:50.172
[ Dramatic music plays ]

1:03:50.206 --> 1:03:51.413
[ Groans ]

1:03:52.413 --> 1:03:54.758
-[ Grunts ]
-JACK: Darlene!

1:03:54.793 --> 1:03:56.206
[ Footsteps approaching ]

1:03:56.241 --> 1:03:58.379
I know you!

1:03:58.413 --> 1:04:01.758
Is this what you want?

1:04:04.413 --> 1:04:06.241
[ Hinges squeaking ]

1:04:06.275 --> 1:04:08.689
[ Wind whistling ]

1:04:08.724 --> 1:04:11.448
-JACK: [ Groaning ]
-[ Door rattling ]

1:04:16.620 --> 1:04:19.551
Darlene!

1:04:19.586 --> 1:04:21.241
[ Door rattling ]

1:04:21.275 --> 1:04:24.241
JACK:
[ Groaning ]

1:04:24.275 --> 1:04:26.551
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

1:04:33.241 --> 1:04:35.206
JACK:
[ Shouting indistinctly ]

1:04:40.517 --> 1:04:42.655
-Oh, God.
-[ Door rattling ]

1:04:42.689 --> 1:04:45.137
Oh, motherfucker.
[ Shouting indistinctly ]

1:04:48.206 --> 1:04:50.172
Aah!

1:04:50.206 --> 1:04:52.241
-[ Gunshot ]
-[ Dramatic music plays ]

1:04:52.275 --> 1:04:54.379
[ Groaning ]

1:04:57.379 --> 1:04:59.172
Darlene!

1:04:59.206 --> 1:05:00.379
[ Laughs ]

1:05:00.413 --> 1:05:03.758
If you died here tonight
as suicide,

1:05:03.793 --> 1:05:06.482
no one would question it!

1:05:06.517 --> 1:05:08.344
All alone on Christmas Eve,

1:05:08.379 --> 1:05:11.620
your daughter missing
for 20 years?

1:05:11.655 --> 1:05:13.758
Come on!

1:05:14.344 --> 1:05:16.586
[ Breathing heavily ]

1:05:23.103 --> 1:05:25.206
[ Groans ]

1:05:40.586 --> 1:05:42.344
Huh.

1:05:49.310 --> 1:05:51.620
Just come out.

1:05:53.724 --> 1:05:57.344
I'll give you one more chance.

1:05:57.379 --> 1:06:02.344
I'll give you the gun,
and we can be done with this!

1:06:05.068 --> 1:06:06.724
Or a knife.

1:06:07.551 --> 1:06:10.517
Would a knife be better?
Huh?

1:06:14.103 --> 1:06:16.551
[ Breathing heavily ]

1:06:20.862 --> 1:06:23.413
Ooh.

1:06:24.517 --> 1:06:26.655
Yeah.

1:06:29.482 --> 1:06:32.137
Look what I found!

1:06:32.172 --> 1:06:34.344
Something a little...
Francais!

1:06:35.448 --> 1:06:39.482
Something I can finally
fucking burn.

1:06:45.241 --> 1:06:47.310
[ Wind whistling ]

1:06:47.344 --> 1:06:49.620
[ Dramatic music plays ]

1:07:02.310 --> 1:07:04.758
[ Sobs softly ]

1:07:17.517 --> 1:07:21.206
Don't make me kill you too.

1:07:21.241 --> 1:07:23.551
[ Music continues ]

1:07:24.793 --> 1:07:27.413
[ Footsteps approaching ]

1:07:30.344 --> 1:07:32.620
[ Music builds, continues ]

1:07:40.172 --> 1:07:43.068
[ Hinges squeaking ]

1:07:44.551 --> 1:07:46.068
Ow!

1:07:46.103 --> 1:07:48.344
[ Dramatic music plays ]

1:07:48.379 --> 1:07:50.620
[ Both grunting ]

1:07:56.344 --> 1:07:59.517
Why?
Why are you making me do this?

1:07:59.551 --> 1:08:02.000
[ Both grunting ]

1:08:07.379 --> 1:08:08.655
[ Gasping ]

1:08:08.689 --> 1:08:10.793
Aah!
[ Groans ]

1:08:10.827 --> 1:08:12.172
[ Grunts ]

1:08:29.620 --> 1:08:31.827
[ Music builds, continues ]

1:08:31.862 --> 1:08:34.206
-[ Footsteps approaching ]
-GRETCHEN: Darlene, look out!

1:08:34.655 --> 1:08:37.034
-Oh, my God!
-Gretch?

1:08:37.068 --> 1:08:39.206
I have never been so happy
to see you.

1:08:39.241 --> 1:08:42.068
Grab me some ribbon.
We've got to get him secured.

1:08:42.103 --> 1:08:43.448
-Here.
-Give me two pieces.

1:08:43.482 --> 1:08:45.068
-Okay, okay!
-Tie that wrist, and make sure

1:08:45.103 --> 1:08:46.689
-it's really, really tight.
-What's happening?

1:08:46.724 --> 1:08:48.206
-Gretchen...
-Yes. What?

1:08:48.241 --> 1:08:49.482
...that was a really
goddamned good shot.

1:08:49.517 --> 1:08:50.793
Oh, God!

1:08:50.827 --> 1:08:54.758
-Shit! Fuck you!
-Oh, shut up. Shut up!

1:08:54.793 --> 1:08:57.241
It doesn't need to be perfect!
Just get it on there!

1:08:57.275 --> 1:08:59.206
-You said tight!
-It's already broken!

1:08:59.241 --> 1:09:00.620
-Okay!
-DARLENE: Okay?

1:09:00.655 --> 1:09:02.482
Help me with this one.
Okay.

1:09:02.517 --> 1:09:05.310
Oh, by the way, Gretchen --
Gretchen, this is Jack.

1:09:05.344 --> 1:09:06.655
-[ Moaning ]
-DARLENE: Jack, Gretchen.

1:09:06.689 --> 1:09:08.517
JackJack?

1:09:08.551 --> 1:09:09.758
DARLENE:
Yeah.

1:09:09.793 --> 1:09:12.206
This is not gonna hold him.
Oh, shit.

1:09:12.241 --> 1:09:14.517
Jesus. What am I doing?
What am I doing?

1:09:14.551 --> 1:09:16.103
-Okay.
-GRETCHEN: No!

1:09:16.137 --> 1:09:17.620
-Where are you going?
-Hey. Hey, lady. Lady.

1:09:17.655 --> 1:09:19.586
She-- She's lost her mind.

1:09:19.620 --> 1:09:21.310
-She -- She tied me up...
-DARLENE: Fuck you.

1:09:21.344 --> 1:09:22.344
...and she shot me.

1:09:22.379 --> 1:09:24.068
[ Thunder rumbling ]

1:09:24.103 --> 1:09:26.379
What is happening?

1:09:27.689 --> 1:09:29.448
Gretch...

1:09:31.137 --> 1:09:32.344
...Sally is dead.

1:09:32.379 --> 1:09:33.586
What?

1:09:33.620 --> 1:09:35.103
What?

1:09:35.137 --> 1:09:37.517
How?
How -- How do you...

1:09:37.551 --> 1:09:39.758
He told me.

1:09:39.793 --> 1:09:41.379
-He told me.
-Oh.

1:09:41.413 --> 1:09:43.379
Oh -- Oh, honey. What can I do?
What can I do?

1:09:43.413 --> 1:09:45.793
I need to get something else
to tie him up with.

1:09:45.827 --> 1:09:47.724
-Don't. Please.
-And you grab that. Grab that.

1:09:47.758 --> 1:09:49.137
-Grab it!
-Ohh.

1:09:49.172 --> 1:09:50.689
Okay.
And if he moves, shoot him.

1:09:50.724 --> 1:09:52.275
-But only in the kneecap, okay?
-Yes.

1:09:52.310 --> 1:09:54.172
-I'll be right back.
-Yes.

1:10:03.413 --> 1:10:06.482
Just because you're scary
doesn't mean I will shoot you.

1:10:07.206 --> 1:10:08.655
Oh, yeah?

1:10:08.689 --> 1:10:10.793
So, where's the safety?

1:10:10.827 --> 1:10:12.172
Right here, asshole.

1:10:16.448 --> 1:10:18.689
[ Clattering ]

1:10:18.724 --> 1:10:21.310
[ Grunts ]

1:10:32.068 --> 1:10:34.103
[ Dramatic music plays ]

1:10:34.137 --> 1:10:36.448
GRETCHEN:
[ Screams ] Darlene!

1:10:36.482 --> 1:10:38.793
-Darlene, get in here!
-[ Gunshot, glass breaking ]

1:10:38.827 --> 1:10:40.517
JACK: [ Grunts,
shouting indistinctly ]

1:10:40.551 --> 1:10:42.413
DARLENE:
Stop! Get off of her!

1:10:42.448 --> 1:10:45.310
Leave her alone!

1:10:45.344 --> 1:10:46.620
No!

1:10:46.655 --> 1:10:48.413
Aah! Ow!

1:10:48.448 --> 1:10:51.275
[ Grunts, breathing heavily ]

1:10:57.241 --> 1:10:59.482
-[ Grunts ]
-[ Body thuds ]

1:11:00.827 --> 1:11:03.448
[ Breathing heavily ]

1:11:07.206 --> 1:11:08.379
Oh, God.

1:11:08.413 --> 1:11:09.586
GRETCHEN:
[ Groans ]

1:11:10.862 --> 1:11:13.068
-Come here.
-Oh. [ Groans ]

1:11:13.103 --> 1:11:15.413
My God.
Are you okay?

1:11:15.827 --> 1:11:17.586
No. Are you?
No!

1:11:17.620 --> 1:11:19.172
Oh, my God.

1:11:19.206 --> 1:11:20.620
Oh!

1:11:20.655 --> 1:11:24.068
Oh. Oh, honey.
Sally.

1:11:24.103 --> 1:11:26.034
-Oh.
-I know. I know. I know.

1:11:26.068 --> 1:11:28.034
I know, but we don't
have time for that.

1:11:28.068 --> 1:11:30.172
Don't! Don't!

1:11:30.206 --> 1:11:31.448
Just be careful.

1:11:31.482 --> 1:11:32.724
-Okay. Okay.
-Careful.

1:11:32.758 --> 1:11:34.103
Okay.

1:11:34.137 --> 1:11:35.310
Okay.

1:11:35.344 --> 1:11:37.448
[ Wood creaking ]

1:11:42.689 --> 1:11:46.482
Okay.
I-I see that he isbreathing.

1:11:46.517 --> 1:11:48.172
We have to call the police.

1:11:48.206 --> 1:11:49.689
No.
No, Gretchen.

1:11:49.724 --> 1:11:51.793
-Yes!
-No. No. Shh!

1:11:51.827 --> 1:11:54.689
We cannot call the police.
He will not talk to the police.

1:11:54.724 --> 1:11:56.517
-He won't.
-Wecan.

1:11:56.551 --> 1:11:58.655
-Wewill talk to the police.
-No. Listen to me.

1:11:58.689 --> 1:12:00.034
We can tell them.
He told you!

1:12:00.068 --> 1:12:01.448
No.
He told me a story,

1:12:01.482 --> 1:12:03.310
but he didn't tell me
the real story, okay?

1:12:03.344 --> 1:12:04.827
He didn't tell me
the whole story.

1:12:04.862 --> 1:12:06.517
He told me it was an accident.

1:12:06.551 --> 1:12:08.137
-That's all.
-Are we gonna leave him here

1:12:08.172 --> 1:12:09.482
when people come over
for Christmas tomorrow?

1:12:09.517 --> 1:12:11.103
-Listen. Listen!
-We are out of our depth.

1:12:11.137 --> 1:12:13.689
Gretchen, please listen to me,
okay?

1:12:13.724 --> 1:12:17.034
I need this.
I need to do this.

1:12:17.068 --> 1:12:20.068
And I just need you
to trust me, okay?

1:12:20.103 --> 1:12:22.206
-Please.
-Okay.

1:12:22.241 --> 1:12:23.827
-Please stay with me.
-Okay. Okay. Okay.

1:12:23.862 --> 1:12:25.310
Of course I will.
Okay.

1:12:25.344 --> 1:12:27.724
Okay.
Okay.

1:12:28.586 --> 1:12:31.103
All right.
Okay.

1:12:31.137 --> 1:12:32.655
GRETCHEN:
This is gonna be heavy as shit.

1:12:32.689 --> 1:12:34.034
DARLENE:
Yeah. I know.

1:12:44.586 --> 1:12:47.827
GRETCHEN: I've done my best
with what we have at hand,

1:12:47.862 --> 1:12:51.310
but you're probably in
a lot of pain.

1:12:51.344 --> 1:12:52.827
His pulse is okay.

1:12:52.862 --> 1:12:54.517
I don't think he's in shock.

1:12:54.551 --> 1:12:57.517
JACK: [ Weakly ]
H-How do you know?

1:12:57.551 --> 1:13:00.689
E.R. nurse, recently retired.

1:13:00.724 --> 1:13:02.241
JACK:
Ah.

1:13:05.482 --> 1:13:08.137
[ Groans weakly ]

1:13:08.172 --> 1:13:09.206
Jack?

1:13:12.379 --> 1:13:15.034
I'm gonna offer you a deal.

1:13:15.655 --> 1:13:18.827
I am going to do what you asked.

1:13:18.862 --> 1:13:21.068
I'll end this for you.

1:13:23.137 --> 1:13:25.724
But I need you to do something
for me.

1:13:25.758 --> 1:13:27.517
Okay.

1:13:27.551 --> 1:13:30.137
Tell me the real story.

1:13:30.172 --> 1:13:31.448
I told you.

1:13:31.482 --> 1:13:35.068
Jack...I need to hear it

1:13:35.103 --> 1:13:38.344
as much as I know
you need to tell it.

1:13:38.379 --> 1:13:41.103
You're just recording this
on her phone, aren't you?

1:13:41.137 --> 1:13:43.172
You're gonna just --
You're gonna turn me in.

1:13:43.206 --> 1:13:44.655
No.
No, no, no.

1:13:44.689 --> 1:13:47.551
Look. Look.
Right here.

1:13:47.586 --> 1:13:50.137
No calls to the cops,

1:13:50.172 --> 1:13:54.620
no calls to family,
no recordings.

1:13:54.655 --> 1:13:57.206
Nothing, okay?

1:13:58.172 --> 1:14:00.689
Shutting it off.

1:14:00.724 --> 1:14:03.068
Putting it right down there.

1:14:04.103 --> 1:14:05.137
That's it.

1:14:05.586 --> 1:14:07.620
It's just us.

1:14:09.655 --> 1:14:11.068
[ Grunts softly ]

1:14:11.103 --> 1:14:13.620
You said you wanted me
to understand.

1:14:15.137 --> 1:14:19.068
But I want us both...
to understand.

1:14:19.103 --> 1:14:21.034
[ Wind whistling ]

1:14:21.482 --> 1:14:24.379
So tell me what you did
to Sally...

1:14:25.448 --> 1:14:26.517
...and why.

1:14:26.551 --> 1:14:29.241
There is no why.

1:14:30.310 --> 1:14:31.551
It just happened.

1:14:31.586 --> 1:14:35.586
Even a storm builds
from something.

1:14:35.620 --> 1:14:39.275
It doesn't just come
out of nowhere.

1:14:40.241 --> 1:14:42.482
So, who's gonna tell her, huh?

1:14:42.517 --> 1:14:46.586
Since honesty is always
the best policy?

1:14:46.620 --> 1:14:48.379
Sorry, Jack.

1:14:48.413 --> 1:14:50.793
She knows all about us.

1:14:50.827 --> 1:14:54.586
Do you think I would've made it
19 years without telling her?

1:14:54.620 --> 1:14:56.620
GRETCHEN:
Did you think I would judge her?

1:14:56.655 --> 1:14:59.172
-How fucking sad are you?
-Okay.

1:14:59.206 --> 1:15:01.379
I would never, ever judge her.

1:15:01.827 --> 1:15:03.103
Oh?

1:15:03.137 --> 1:15:04.586
[ Chuckles weakly ]

1:15:04.620 --> 1:15:07.379
Oh, so maybe there's
another reason

1:15:07.413 --> 1:15:09.103
you'll drop anything
for Darlene.

1:15:09.137 --> 1:15:11.827
I mean, believe me.
I get it.

1:15:11.862 --> 1:15:15.034
She is...enthralling.

1:15:15.068 --> 1:15:17.448
And I remember you now.

1:15:17.482 --> 1:15:19.379
You were Don Sullivan's wife,
right?

1:15:19.413 --> 1:15:21.448
His drunk wife.
And no wonder.

1:15:21.482 --> 1:15:23.241
I mean, having to live
with that.

1:15:23.275 --> 1:15:25.793
Making all those kids with
a man, playing the good wife.

1:15:25.827 --> 1:15:30.103
You never had a chance
in this town, did you, baby?

1:15:30.137 --> 1:15:31.448
-Huh?
-DARLENE: Hey, listen.

1:15:31.482 --> 1:15:33.103
Look at me.
That was meant to scandalize me.

1:15:33.137 --> 1:15:35.172
-It doesn't.
-So you want to talk about why?

1:15:35.206 --> 1:15:37.206
-Unconditional.
-You want to talk about why?

1:15:37.241 --> 1:15:40.517
So let's talk about
why Sally got in my truck.

1:15:40.551 --> 1:15:41.793
Okay. Tell me.

1:15:41.827 --> 1:15:43.655
You were drunk all the time.

1:15:43.689 --> 1:15:45.724
-Mm-hmm.
-Ed had gone full ostrich.

1:15:45.758 --> 1:15:47.310
He'd shut down.

1:15:47.344 --> 1:15:49.517
If you hadn't been such
a fucking mess, maybe --

1:15:49.551 --> 1:15:52.413
Okay. Great.
That is a great place to start.

1:15:52.448 --> 1:15:54.655
Okay.
She got in your truck.

1:15:54.689 --> 1:15:56.517
And then you told me

1:15:56.551 --> 1:15:58.482
you suggested driving
out to the lake.

1:15:58.517 --> 1:15:59.724
You laid down a blanket,

1:15:59.758 --> 1:16:01.275
and then she started talking
about me.

1:16:01.310 --> 1:16:03.655
-What did she say?
-Darlene.

1:16:03.689 --> 1:16:06.379
No.
It's okay.

1:16:06.413 --> 1:16:08.586
Can you remember
her exact words?

1:16:08.620 --> 1:16:09.793
JACK:
Yeah, I do.

1:16:09.827 --> 1:16:13.068
I do, actually.

1:16:13.103 --> 1:16:15.517
I remember her saying,

1:16:15.551 --> 1:16:18.689
"I wish you could see the woman
that we see.

1:16:19.793 --> 1:16:26.068
Maybe then she'd finally stop
at just be her already."

1:16:28.137 --> 1:16:32.103
I know you, Darlene,
and I know what you need.

1:16:32.137 --> 1:16:33.655
Jack, don't go down this road.

1:16:33.689 --> 1:16:36.724
You've been practicing
in your head all these years

1:16:36.758 --> 1:16:40.068
what you'd do
to whoever took Sally.

1:16:40.103 --> 1:16:42.551
Now this is what you can do
for her now.

1:16:42.586 --> 1:16:45.034
I'm here, so do it.

1:16:45.068 --> 1:16:48.172
Listen to me very carefully.

1:16:48.206 --> 1:16:51.137
You tell me the full story --
and I mean everything --

1:16:51.172 --> 1:16:56.034
I mean every little detail --
and it's the gun.

1:16:56.068 --> 1:17:00.241
But if you keep bobbing
and weaving and dodging,

1:17:00.275 --> 1:17:02.655
then I start making calls.

1:17:02.689 --> 1:17:05.206
So it's completely up to you.

1:17:05.241 --> 1:17:07.758
It's your choice.

1:17:09.172 --> 1:17:11.793
You said you came here
to help me.

1:17:13.586 --> 1:17:15.655
This is what I need.

1:17:16.551 --> 1:17:22.758
This is how I can finally say
goodbye to Sally.

1:17:24.413 --> 1:17:27.379
So h-help me.

1:17:30.068 --> 1:17:32.517
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

1:17:37.586 --> 1:17:41.413
Promise me
you'll pull the trigger.

1:17:44.862 --> 1:17:46.241
Yes.
I promise.

1:17:46.275 --> 1:17:49.620
I...I promise.

1:17:53.551 --> 1:17:55.000
Okay.

1:17:57.206 --> 1:17:58.793
Okay.

1:18:02.482 --> 1:18:04.000
Okay.

1:18:06.137 --> 1:18:08.310
Okay.
[ Inhales sharply ]

1:18:10.068 --> 1:18:12.310
Do you really believe...

1:18:13.551 --> 1:18:17.758
...that Sally wanted
to kiss you?

1:18:17.793 --> 1:18:20.137
[ Music continues ]

1:18:21.793 --> 1:18:23.206
No.

1:18:28.172 --> 1:18:30.586
But I thought it would be okay.

1:18:32.586 --> 1:18:37.482
And do you really think...
that she kissed you back?

1:18:37.517 --> 1:18:39.241
She did.
She did it first.

1:18:39.275 --> 1:18:42.275
And I-I w-- I w-- Really,
I wondered about that a lot.

1:18:42.310 --> 1:18:43.793
You know, why did she do that?

1:18:43.827 --> 1:18:45.413
Was it just, you know, instinct?

1:18:45.448 --> 1:18:47.275
You know, someone --
someone kisses you

1:18:47.310 --> 1:18:51.172
and you just -- you'd be --
you kiss them back.

1:18:51.206 --> 1:18:54.137
DARLENE:
Because she was so afraid.

1:18:57.586 --> 1:19:00.206
What did she do next?

1:19:01.586 --> 1:19:03.068
She'd, uh...

1:19:04.862 --> 1:19:06.620
She taken off her jacket.

1:19:06.655 --> 1:19:11.241
It was freakishly warm
for December.

1:19:11.275 --> 1:19:15.724
And she had on this...
loose-fitting dress,

1:19:15.758 --> 1:19:19.344
and I...I pulled it down.

1:19:19.379 --> 1:19:21.344
And -- And -- And...

1:19:22.206 --> 1:19:24.241
And I --

1:19:24.275 --> 1:19:28.241
She was laid out across
the blanket and into the grass.

